model_response.argument:
Applicant respectfully traverses the rejection under 35 USC 102(a)(1).

Doudna is a foundational CRISPR-Cas9 reference. The claimed composition uses Cas12a (formerly Cpf1) — a different nuclease with distinct properties. Cas12a uses a different PAM sequence (TTTV vs NGG), generates staggered cuts (vs blunt cuts from Cas9), and uses a single crRNA without tracrRNA. Doudna does not disclose Cas12a.

Further, even setting aside the nuclease difference, Doudna does not disclose:
(1) A guide targeting PCSK9 exon 3 specifically — Doudna's examples target different genes;
(2) A donor template encoding P.Leu22del — a specific loss-of-function variant associated with reduced LDL cholesterol;
(3) DLin-MC3-DMA lipid nanoparticle delivery — Doudna uses electroporation;
(4) Greater than 50% HDR efficiency in human hepatocytes — Doudna reports ~5-10% HDR in different cell types.

The claim recites a specific, multicomponent composition. Four independent elements are absent from Doudna. Anticipation requires that a single reference disclose every element of the claim. Doudna discloses none of the four distinguishing elements.

For these reasons, Claim 1 is not anticipated.

Applicant respectfully traverses the rejection under 35 USC 101.

Step 2A, Prong 1: Applicant acknowledges that the correlation between biomarkers and treatment response involves natural phenomena. However, the claim as a whole is not directed to observing a natural correlation — it is directed to a specific, multi-step diagnostic method that applies specific measurement techniques to generate a clinically actionable result.

Step 2A, Prong 2: The claim integrates any natural correlation into a practical application through specific, non-conventional techniques:

(1) Measuring ctDNA levels specifically via digital droplet PCR targeting BRAF V600E — this is a specific measurement technique, not a generic 'detecting' step;
(2) Computing TMB from ctDNA using a 500+ gene targeted panel — this specifies the scope and methodology of the measurement;
(3) Computing a composite response score as a weighted combination of three specific biomarkers — this is a specific mathematical transformation, not a mere observation;
(4) Classifying based on a threshold derived from a 200+ patient training cohort — this specifies the statistical basis for the decision.

This is analogous to the claims found patent-eligible in Vanda Pharmaceuticals Inc. v. West-Ward Pharmaceuticals Int'l Ltd., 887 F.3d 1117 (Fed. Cir. 2018), where the claim applied a natural relationship to a specific treatment protocol.

Step 2B: The specific combination of digital droplet PCR for BRAF V600E, 500-gene TMB panel, and composite scoring from a trained cohort represents an inventive concept. While each measurement technique may be individually known, the specific combination into a composite score with trained thresholds is not conventional for melanoma immunotherapy response prediction.

For these reasons, Claim 1 is patent-eligible.

test_cases.original_claim:
1. A method for generating recommendations comprising:
  receiving user interaction data;
  generating user embeddings from the interaction data;
  computing similarity scores between user embeddings;
  generating a ranked list of recommendations based on the similarity scores.

model_response.amended_claim:
1. (Currently Amended) A method for generating recommendations comprising:
  receiving user interaction data comprising implicit feedback signals including dwell time, scroll depth, and interaction sequences;
  generating user embeddings from the interaction data using a variational autoencoder that maps interaction sequences to a latent space with a learned prior distribution;
  computing similarity scores between user embeddings using an attention-weighted cosine similarity that dynamically adjusts similarity weighting based on the user's current session context;
  generating a ranked list of recommendations based on the similarity scores; and
  re-ranking the recommendations using a diversity-aware objective function that penalizes redundant items based on item-item similarity in the latent space.

test_cases.original_claim:
1. A power converter comprising:
  an input stage receiving DC power;
  a switching stage with a plurality of switches;
  an output stage providing regulated DC power;
  a controller driving the switching stage.

model_response.amended_claim:
1. (Currently Amended) A power converter comprising:
  an input stage receiving DC power;
  a switching stage with a plurality of GaN HEMT switches operating at a switching frequency above 1 MHz;
  an output stage providing regulated DC power;
  a controller driving the switching stage, the controller comprising:
    a predictive dead-time optimizer that dynamically adjusts dead-time intervals between complementary switch transitions based on real-time measurement of body diode conduction duration, and
    a current-mode control loop with a sensorless current estimation circuit that computes inductor current from the on-state resistance of the GaN HEMT switches without a discrete current sense resistor.

test_cases.original_claim:
1. A method of managing inventory comprising:
  receiving inventory data from a plurality of locations;
  determining reorder points for each item;
  generating purchase orders when inventory falls below reorder points;
  transmitting the purchase orders to suppliers.

model_response.amended_claim:
1. (Currently Amended) A method of managing inventory [[comprising]] performed by a distributed computing system comprising edge computing nodes deployed at each of a plurality of warehouse locations, the method comprising:
  receiving, at each edge computing node, real-time inventory data from RFID sensors and computer vision cameras monitoring shelf positions;
  each edge computing node locally executing a demand forecasting model comprising a temporal convolutional network trained on the location's historical demand patterns to determine dynamic reorder points that adapt to seasonal patterns, promotional events, and local demand trends;
  the edge computing nodes communicating updated reorder points to a central coordination server that performs cross-location inventory optimization using a mixed-integer linear programming solver to minimize total supply chain cost;
  the central coordination server generating purchase orders when aggregated network-wide inventory, as computed by the MILP solver, falls below the optimized reorder points; and
  transmitting the purchase orders to suppliers via an API integration layer.
